<item>
            <title>[SEC-325] Add support for Groups</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-325</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?p=53307&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?p=53307&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;quote from=&quot;raible&quot;&amp;gt;I attended a BOF at The Spring Experience where there was much debate about having a &quot;Groups&quot; concept in Acegi. Colin was for it, Ben against. However, in the end, I believe Ben said it&apos;d only take 10 minutes to add - so he&apos;d do it.&amp;lt;/quote&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;quote from=&quot;alex&quot;&amp;gt;It&apos;s a semantic thing. People who want an &quot;administrative&quot; / &quot;management&quot; interface for security would like to see groups etc. I would not modify the GrantedAuthority concept to not recognise groups - I would merely add a GROUP table which the out-of-the-box DAOs would recognise and then generate additional GrantedAuthority[]s accordingly.&amp;lt;/quote&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
